 Yorkshire, England":"York, Jórvík, England","York, Yorkshire, Inglaterra":"York, Jórvík, England","Oxfordshire, Inglaterra, Reino Unido":"Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1384– 1440":"1384–1440","1384–1440":"1384–1440","1390–Female":"1390–Overleden","1405–1457":"1405–1457","1341–Male":"1341–Overleden","1369–Female":"1369–Overleden","1369":"1369","1457":"1457"," 1440":"1440","1341":"1341","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","Abt 1405":"circa 1405","1390":"1390","1405":"1405","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, England","York, Yorkshire, Inglaterra":"York, Yorkshire, England","Oxfordshire, Inglaterra, Reino Unido":"Oxfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1384– 1440":"1384–1440","1384–1440":"1384–1440","1390–Female":"1390–Deceased","1405–1457":"1405–1457","1341–Male":"1341–Deceased","1369–Female":"1369–Deceased","1369":"1369","1457":"1457"," 1440":"1440","1341":"1341","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","Abt 1405":"about 1405","1390":"1390","1405":"1405","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, England","York, Yorkshire, Inglaterra":"York, Yorkshire, England","Oxfordshire, Inglaterra, Reino Unido":"Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Whitton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Whitton in Morebattle (Roxburghshire). The placename is from Old English <i>hwīt</i> ‘white’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farm, village’, as with many of the places in 2 below.","English: habitational name from any of the places called Whitton (Durham, Lincolnshire, Middlesex, Northumberland, Shropshire, Suffolk) or Witton (Cheshire, Durham, Lancashire, Herefordshire, Norfolk, Northumberland, Warwickshire, Worcestershire, North Yorkshire); or possibly from Wyton (Huntingdonshire, East Yorkshire); or possibly from Weeton, Market Weighton, or Little Weighton (East Yorkshire). The placenames do not all share the same etymology but most of their post-medieval spellings are interchangeable. Most of the placenames derive from the Old English personal name <i>Hwīta</i> or Old English <i>hwīt</i> ‘white’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, though some, for example Witton in Warwickshire, derive from Old English <i>wīc</i> ‘dwelling, specialized farmstead’ + <i>tūn</i>, and some others, for example Witton in Norfolk, derive from Old English <i>widu</i> ‘wood’ + <i>tūn</i>. Whitton in Lincolnshire derives from the Old English personal name <i>Hwīta</i> (genitive <i>Hwītan</i>) or Old English <i>hwīt</i> (dative <i>hwītan</i>) + <i>ēg</i> ‘island’. Witton in Lancashire derives from the Old English personal <i>Witta</i> + Old English <i>tūn</i>.","English: in Devon, this surname is a variant of   Whiddon  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Whitten","meanings":["English: variant of   Whitton   or   Whiting  ."]},{"name":"Whetten","meanings":["English, Scottish, or northern Irish: variant of   Whitton  ."]},{"name":"Whiddon","meanings":["English (Devon): habitational name from any of numerous minor places in Devon named Whiddon. Some are named with Old English <i>hwīt</i> ‘white’ + <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’ or <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’; others with Old English <i>hwǣte</i> ‘wheat’ + <i>dūn</i> or <i>denu</i> ‘valley’."]},{"name":"Whiton","meanings":["English (Essex): variant of   Whitton  . This surname is now rare in Britain.","History: James Whiton of Hingham, Norfolk, England, came to Plymouth, MA, in 1635."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Whitton was born in 1384, in York, Yorkshire, England, his father, Robtus Whitton, was 43 and his mother, señora Whitton, was 15. He married Katerine De Whyton about 1405. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1440, in his hometown, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1384– 1440":"1384–1440","1384–1440":"1384–1440","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1405–1457":"1405–1457","1341–Male":"1341–Surnud","1369–Female":"1369–Surnud","1369":"1369","1457":"1457"," 1440":"1440","1341":"1341","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","Abt 1405":"umbes 1405","1390":"1390","1405":"1405","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, England","York, Yorkshire, Inglaterra":"York, Yorkshire, England","Oxfordshire, Inglaterra, Reino Unido":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1384– 1440":"1384–1440","1384–1440":"1384–1440","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1405–1457":"1405–1457","1341–Male":"1341–Kuollut","1369–Female":"1369–Kuollut","1369":"1369","1457":"1457"," 1440":"1440","1341":"1341","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","Abt 1405":"noin 1405","1390":"1390","1405":"1405","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, England","York, Yorkshire, Inglaterra":"York, Yorkshire, England","Oxfordshire, Inglaterra, Reino Unido":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1384– 1440":"1384–1440","1384–1440":"1384–1440","1390–Female":"1390–Décédée","1405–1457":"1405–1457","1341–Male":"1341–Décédé","1369–Female":"1369–Décédée","1369":"1369","1457":"1457"," 1440":"1440","1341":"1341","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","Abt 1405":"environ 1405","1390":"1390","1405":"1405","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Everwyck, Angleterre","York, Yorkshire, Inglaterra":"York, Everwyck, Angleterre","Oxfordshire, Inglaterra, Reino Unido":"Oxfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Thomas Whitton est né en 1384, à York, Everwyck, Angleterre, son père, Robtus Whitton, avait 43 ans et sa mère, señora Whitton, avait 15 ans. Il a épousé Katerine De Whyton environ 1405. Ils ont eu au moins